uch the item he was seeking for so much time.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Rolen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Dumb paladins  <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/smile.gif"><P>A. if you increased spawn rate of items or anyhting to that effect, or you made an item obtainable by everyone, and not just by the people with 5 hours a day to play, then why would the items be sought after?<P>B. everquest isn't a democracy you get what you get<P>C. REAL LIFE... some people have parents (higher chars) who give them what they want, like cars, education, games, whatever, spoil them... and there are parents who don't care at all, and just leave the kids to fend for themselves.<P>Rolen<BR>~Necromancer (hence the dumb pally part) of Tallon Zek~<P>P.s. Killed a (dumb) yellow pally the other day in a duel, and still had half mana  <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/smile.gif"> (without useing dark pact series either)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Fogia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Answer to last post :<P>A- I didnt say to increase the rate. I said find a way to limit (stop) the high lvl carac or class that dont need this item to camp it for money or twinked carac. There are many ways to do it.<P>B- Ok I agree this : you need to be lucky. But dont forget its a game and if you want to keep the maximum people playing you have to provide them REACHABLE goals. Do you think many people will play for example shadowknight if these have a special armor that requiered for each part to kill a dragon  while this armor is consider as 'mid lvl armor' ?<P>C- Ok lets stop this topic about RL. This is stupid. RL is RL and EQ is a game : you cant compare them.<P>Fogia<BR>Lvl 34 paladin</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
